34
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:46,383
[SPEAKER_16]: had made some motions to make amendments to it.

35
00:01:46,824 --> 00:01:52,348
[SPEAKER_16]: We also had some proposed changes from Attorney Stein at KP Law that we considered at our June meeting.

36
00:01:53,168 --> 00:02:09,441
[SPEAKER_16]: And there were also some comments from, you know, members of the city staff, as well as counselors, for example, and members of the public, but just an example of that is Commissioner McGivern had raised a concern about staffing levels needed to administer this ordinance.

37
00:02:11,085 --> 00:02:13,586
[SPEAKER_16]: you know, members of the public had had raised some concerns.

38
00:02:13,666 --> 00:02:19,487
[SPEAKER_16]: Councilors had raised some concerns about the regulation of trees on private way and private property.

39
00:02:20,628 --> 00:02:31,551
[SPEAKER_16]: And at the conclusion of that meeting, the city council moved to request that the city solicitor and our legal council take the proposed language of the tree preservation protection and replacement ordinance.

40
00:02:32,091 --> 00:02:46,725
[SPEAKER_16]: and properly place the proposed changes within Medford's existing city ordinances that included changes to existing ordinance language regarding public shade trees that fall under chapter 87, creating a proposed general zoning ordinance for the protection of certain trees on private property.

41
00:02:47,705 --> 00:02:55,707
[SPEAKER_16]: separating section six into a tree committee ordinance, a separate tree committee ordinance that would be placed in chapter two, article three of Benford's ordinances.

42
00:02:56,468 --> 00:03:08,071
[SPEAKER_16]: And that would also include any other suggestions or proposed amendments that legal counsel deemed necessary while preserving the intent of the proposed language discussed at the council at our June meeting.

43
00:03:09,291 --> 00:03:13,773
[SPEAKER_16]: My understanding is that we received a communication

44
00:03:16,175 --> 00:03:27,746
